An accessible app is usable by anyone, regardless of impairments in vision, mobility, or hearing.

### TalkBack

It is an Android screen reader app made by Google.
It speaks out the content of the screen based on what the user is doing.
The green outline indicates which UI element has accessibility focus.
Single press(tap) gives an element accessibility focus.
Double-tapping anywhere on the screen activates the element that has focus.

### Explore by Touch Mode

When this mode is enabled, device will speak information about an item immediately after its pressed.

** Compose built-in UI elements also support TalkBack .

### Linear navigation by swiping

Swiping right: Moves accessibility focus to the next item on screen.
Swiping left: Moves accessibility focus to previous item on screen.

**Emulator can use keyboard arrow keys to mimic this behaviour.

Swiping with two finger from bottom of device: Navigates to Home Screen
Two finger swipe from left to right edge of device: Back navigation
Two finger: Scroll

### Making Non-Text Elements Readable by Talkback

Adding content descriptions:  This specifies details for Talkback to read by adding a content description. It is a piece of text that describes the view and is read by Talkback.

### Making a View focusable

We can make view focusable, by setting its android:focusable attribute to true or by adding click listener or adding contentDescription. In compose this same can be achieved using modifiers.

### Creating a Comparable Experience

If there is a view that does not provide any value other than decoration, we should explicitly tell Talkback to ignore it by setting the android:importantForAccessibility to no.

### Accessibility Scanner

Google’s this app, analyses apps and evaluates how accessible they are, and provides suggestions based on its findings.
Eg: Touch target: Minimum size for all touch targets is 48dp.

** View.announceForAccessibility(…) to announce what happened as a result of action happening.
Eg: Making announcement when we get the result back from taking a photo
